                <h1>Security at Darpan</h1>
                <p>Your security and privacy are our top priorities. Learn about our comprehensive security measures.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="security-section">
                <h2>End-to-End Encryption</h2>
                <p>All video meetings on Darpan are secured with end-to-end encryption. This means that your conversations, shared files, and messages can only be seen by meeting participants, not by Darpan or any third parties.</p>
                
                <h3>Key Security Features</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>AES 256-bit encryption for all data transmission</li>
                    <li>Unique encryption keys for each meeting session</li>
                    <li>Secure key exchange protocols</li>
                    <li>No persistent storage of meeting content</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="security-section">
                <h2>Meeting Access Controls</h2>
                <h3>Meeting Protection</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Unique meeting IDs for every session</li>
                    <li>Optional meeting passwords</li>
                    <li>Waiting room feature for participant screening</li>
                    <li>Host controls for participant management</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3>Host Controls</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Ability to remove participants</li>
                    <li>Meeting lock option</li>
                    <li>Screen sharing permissions</li>
                    <li>Chat and file sharing controls</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="security-section">
                <h2>Data Protection</h2>
                <p>We implement multiple layers of security to protect your data:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Regular security audits and penetration testing</li>
                    <li>Compliance with international data protection standards</li>
                    <li>Secure data centers with physical security measures</li>
                    <li>Regular software updates and security patches</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="security-section">
                <h2>Best Practices for Users</h2>
                <h3>Meeting Security Tips</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Use unique meeting IDs for each session</li>
                    <li>Enable waiting room for sensitive meetings</li>
                    <li>Share meeting links securely</li>
                    <li>Keep your Darpan application updated</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3>Account Security</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Use strong, unique passwords</li>
                    <li>Enable two-factor authentication</li>
                    <li>Regularly review your security settings</li>
                    <li>Log out from shared devices</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="security-section">
                <h2>Reporting Security Issues</h2>
                <p>If you discover a security vulnerability or have concerns about the security of your account, please contact our security team immediately at security@darpan.com. We take all security reports seriously and will investigate promptly.</p>
            </div>

